    73Ôćĺ## Installation
    75Ôćĺ```sh
    76Ôćĺ> npm install neverthrow
    77Ôćĺ```
    78Ôćĺ
    79Ôćĺ## Recommended: Use `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`
    81ÔćĺAs part of `neverthrow`s [bounty program](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/issues/314), user [mdbetancourt](https://github.com/mdbetancourt) created [`eslint-plugin-neverthrow`](https://github.com/mdbetancourt/eslint-plugin-neverthrow) to ensure that errors are not gone unhandled.
    82Ôćĺ
    83ÔćĺInstall by running:
    84Ôćĺ
    85Ôćĺ```sh
    86Ôćĺ> npm install eslint-plugin-neverthrow
    87Ôćĺ```
    88Ôćĺ
    89ÔćĺWith `eslint-plugin-neverthrow`, you are forced to consume the result in one of the following three ways:
    90Ôćĺ
    91Ôćĺ- Calling `.match`
    92Ôćĺ- Calling `.unwrapOr`
    93Ôćĺ- Calling `._unsafeUnwrap`
    94Ôćĺ
    95ÔćĺThis ensures that you're explicitly handling the error of your `Result`.
    96Ôćĺ
    97ÔćĺThis plugin is essentially a porting of Rust's [`must-use`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/result/#results-must-be-used) attribute. 
    98Ôćĺ
    99Ôćĺ
   100Ôćĺ## Top-Level API
   102Ôćĺ`neverthrow` exposes the following:
   103Ôćĺ
   104Ôćĺ- `ok` convenience function to create an `Ok` variant of `Result`
   105Ôćĺ- `err` convenience function to create an `Err` variant of `Result`
   106Ôćĺ- `Ok` class and type
   107Ôćĺ- `Err` class and type
   108Ôćĺ- `Result` Type as well as namespace / object from which to call [`Result.fromThrowable`](#resultfromthrowable-static-class-method), [Result.combine](#resultcombine-static-class-method).
   109Ôćĺ- `ResultAsync` class
   110Ôćĺ- `okAsync` convenience function to create a `ResultAsync` containing an `Ok` type `Result`
   111Ôćĺ- `errAsync` convenience function to create a `ResultAsync` containing an `Err` type `Result`
   112Ôćĺ
   113Ôćĺ```typescript
   114Ôćĺimport {
   115Ôćĺ  ok,
   116Ôćĺ  Ok,
   117Ôćĺ  err,
   118Ôćĺ  Err,
   119Ôćĺ  Result,
   120Ôćĺ  okAsync,
   121Ôćĺ  errAsync,
   122Ôćĺ  ResultAsync,
   123Ôćĺ  fromAsyncThrowable,
   124Ôćĺ  fromThrowable,
   125Ôćĺ  fromPromise,
   126Ôćĺ  fromSafePromise,
   127Ôćĺ  safeTry,
   128Ôćĺ} from 'neverthrow'
   129Ôćĺ```
   130Ôćĺ
   131Ôćĺ---
   132Ôćĺ
   133Ôćĺ**Check out the [wiki](https://github.com/supermacro/neverthrow/wiki) for help on how to make the most of `neverthrow`.**
   134Ôćĺ
   135ÔćĺIf you find this package useful, please consider [sponsoring me](https://github.com/sponsors/supermacro/) or simply [buying me a coffee](https://ko-fi.com/gdelgado)!
